Final Assessment

You now have the architectural foundation for an exceptionally ambitious platform. The challenge is no longer deciding what to build—it's deciding what to build first.

If your objective is to create a company that can realistically compete in the enterprise financial software market, the highest-return investment now is not another architecture document. It is:

A production-ready core platform (Identity, Workflow, Integration, Data, Observability).
One exceptional business domain (for example, Lending + Finance for NBFCs).
A consistent design system and developer platform.
An incremental roadmap that delivers customer value every few months.

That approach gives you a product customers can adopt while leaving room to evolve toward the larger long-term vision you've outlined.